modules.description: This module provides functions to read files and parse their metadata using Yaml, specifically handling metadata extraction strategies. It operates on file paths and data types that implement the `DATA_READABLE` interface, returning parsed metadata alongside file content or metadata-only results. Concrete use cases include extracting front matter from Yaml files or processing configuration files where metadata is embedded at the start of the file.

This module provides functions to read and parse files containing metadata in Yaml format, extracting both the metadata and the file content. It works with Yaml data structures and file paths, supporting metadata extraction strategies for source or target contexts. Concrete use cases include loading configuration files or data files where metadata is embedded in the file itself.

This module provides functions to parse YAML metadata from files, extracting both metadata and content or metadata alone. It works with YAML values and file paths, supporting use cases like reading configuration files or front matter from text files. Key operations include parsing YAML strings, normalizing metadata into a standard format, and reading files with configurable metadata extraction strategies.
